  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\"><img alt=\"Tyrosh.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/50px-Tyrosh.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/75px-Tyrosh.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/100px-Tyrosh.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">The dwarf juggler</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\"><img alt=\"Tyrosh.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/50px-Tyrosh.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/75px-Tyrosh.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/100px-Tyrosh.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nthe juggler<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/300_AC\" title=\"300 AC\">300&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyrosh</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>dwarf juggler</b> was an entertainer in <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyrosh</a>. His given name is unknown.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dwarf_juggler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Dwarf\" title=\"Dwarf\">dwarf</a> was an old man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He was bald, and had brown eyes. He may have had <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> teeth, or they may have fallen out with age.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Because he was old, his hands were not as dexterous as they used to be, so he occasionally dropped the balls he was juggling and had to chase them, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Tyroshi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tyroshi\">Tyroshi</a> would laugh and throw him <a href=\"/index.php/Coin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coin\">coins</a> nevertheless.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dwarf_juggler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The juggler entertained people every day for years at the square by the <a href=\"/index.php/Fountain_of_the_Drunken_God\" title=\"Fountain of the Drunken God\">Fountain of the Drunken God</a> in Tyrosh. He was known to a pair of dwarf entertainers, <a href=\"/index.php/Oppo\" title=\"Oppo\">Oppo</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Penny\" title=\"Penny\">Penny</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dwarf_juggler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dwarf_juggler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> offers a <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lordship</a> to anyone who brings her the head of her dwarf brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> who had been found guilty of the murder of her son, King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey Baratheon</a>, but escaped.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Cersei's bounty results in the murder of a number of innocent dwarfs and children throughout <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>A <a href=\"/index.php/Tyroshi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tyroshi\">Tyroshi</a> with a forked beard <a href=\"/index.php/Hair_dye\" title=\"Hair dye\">dyed</a> green and pink presents Cersei with an elaborate chest, made of cedar, inlaid with <a href=\"/index.php/Ivory\" title=\"Ivory\">ivory</a> in a pattern of vines and flowers, with hinges and clasps of white <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a>. Inside is a dwarf's head on a bed of blue velvet, which Cersei immediately recognizes as not Tyrion's. The dwarf has brown eyes, whereas Tyrion's are green and black, though the Tyroshi claims he replaced Tyrion's eyes with glass ones when they started to rot. Cersei also notes that the dwarf is twice her brother's age and bald, and his teeth are missing. The Tyroshi claims the dwarf had gold teeth, which he removed. He protests that the dwarf has no nose, the same as Tyrion, and Cersei points out that he cut the dwarf's nose off. For the Tyroshi's fraud, Cersei has him sent to <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a> to have his own nose cut off.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dwarf_juggler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>On the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Selaesori_Qhoran\" title=\"Selaesori Qhoran\">Selaesori Qhoran</a></i> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Sea\" title=\"Summer Sea\">Summer Sea</a>, Penny tells Tyrion that the night he was arrested for Joffrey's murder at <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_Wedding\" title=\"Purple Wedding\">his wedding</a>, she and her brother Oppo left King's Landing in fear someone might suspect them of being involved. They went to Tyrosh, which they hoped was far enough away, and where they knew another dwarf, the juggler. One morning, they heard that the juggler had been murdered and his body was found at the <a href=\"/index.php/Temple_of_Trios\" title=\"Temple of Trios\">Temple of Trios</a>. He had been cut into three parts, each part placed into one of the mouths of the statue of <a href=\"/index.php/Trios\" title=\"Trios\">Trios</a> by the temple doors. However, when the parts were sewn back together, his head was missing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Penny blames Tyrion for the old man's death, as she does for Oppo, who was also murdered by Cersei's bounty hunters. Tyrion says he is sorry for both of their deaths, but the blame is on Cersei and her bounty hunters, not him. Penny throws her <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a> in his face, and leaves the room.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dwarf_juggler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Your head may have glass eyes, but I do not. There are <a href=\"/index.php/Gargoyle\" title=\"Gargoyle\">gargoyles</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> that look more like <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">the Imp</a> than this creature.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>, to the <a href=\"/index.php/Tyroshi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tyroshi\">Tyroshi</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Tyroshi:</b> An honest mistake. One <a href=\"/index.php/Dwarf\" title=\"Dwarf\">dwarf</a> looks so much like another, and... Your Grace will observe, he has no nose...<br />\n<b>Cersei:</b> He has no nose because you <i>cut it off</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;the <a href=\"/index.php/Tyroshi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tyroshi\">Tyroshi</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Penny:</b> Are you sorry about the juggler too?<br />\n</p><p><b>Tyrion:</b> I never knew your juggler existed until this very moment... but yes, I am sorry he is dead.<br />\n<b>Penny:</b> He died for you. His blood is on your hands.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Tyrion:</b> His blood is on <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">my sister's</a> hands, and the hands of the brutes who killed him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Penny\" title=\"Penny\">Penny</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>My hands... my hands are crusted with old blood, aye. Call me <a href=\"/index.php/Kinslayer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kinslayer\">kinslayer</a>, and you won't be wrong. <a href=\"/index.php/Kingslayer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kingslayer\">Kingslayer</a>, I'll answer to that one as well. [...] But I have never killed a juggler, nor a <a href=\"/index.php/Dwarf\" title=\"Dwarf\">dwarf</a>, and I am not to blame for what happened to <a href=\"/index.php/Oppo\" title=\"Oppo\">your bloody brother</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Penny\" title=\"Penny\">Penny</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dwarf_juggler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\">1.7</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_33\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 33\">Chapter 33</a>, Tyrion VIII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc36.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\">2.5</